🧠 What is Node.js?

Node.js is a **JavaScript runtime environment** that allows developers to run JavaScript **on the server side**.

Before Node.js:

```text
JavaScript → Browser only
```

After Node.js:

```text
JavaScript → Browser + Server
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Features of Node.js

✔ Fast execution (V8 Engine)
✔ Non-blocking I/O
✔ Event-driven architecture
✔ Single-threaded event loop
✔ Huge npm ecosystem

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Node.js Event Loop

Node.js uses an **event loop** to handle multiple requests efficiently.

Flow:

```text
Client Request → Event Loop → Callback Queue → Response
```

This allows Node.js to process many requests without creating multiple threads.

