🔷 Creating a Basic Node Server

Create file:

```text
server.js
```

Code:

```javascript
const http = require("http");

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  res.write("Welcome to Node.js Server");
  res.end();
});

server.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log("Server running on port 3000");
});
```

Run:

```bash
node server.js
```

Visit:

```text
http://localhost:3000
```

